frequency.name: frequency
frequency.comment: Frequency of the elapsed counter in Hz.

reset.name: reset
reset.comment:
Resets the angular-core.AvgStopwatch.elapsed count to zero.

This method does not stop or start the dart-core.Stopwatch.

elapsedTicks.name: elapsedTicks
elapsedTicks.comment:
Returns the elapsed number of clock ticks since calling angular-core.AvgStopwatch.start while the dart-core.Stopwatch is running.

Returns the elapsed number of clock ticks between calling angular-core.AvgStopwatch.start and calling angular-core.AvgStopwatch.stop.

Returns 0 if the dart-core.Stopwatch has never been started.

The elapsed number of clock ticks increases by dart-core.Stopwatch.frequency every second.

hashCode.name: hashCode
hashCode.comment:
Get a hash code for this object.

All objects have hash codes. Hash codes are guaranteed to be the same for objects that are equal when compared using the equality operator ==. Other than that there are no guarantees about the hash codes. They will not be consistent between runs and there are no distribution guarantees.

If a subclass overrides angular-core.AvgStopwatch.hashCode it should override the equality operator as well to maintain consistency.

isRunning.name: isRunning
isRunning.comment: Returns wether the StopWatch is currently running.

runtimeType.name: runtimeType
runtimeType.comment: A representation of the runtime type of the object.

==.comment:
The equality operator.

The default behavior for all dart-core.Objects is to return true if and only if this and angular-core.AvgStopwatch.==.other are the same object.

Override this method to specify a different equality relation on a class. The overriding method must still be an equivalence relation. That is, it must be:

  • Total: It must return a boolean for all arguments. It should never throw or return null.

  • Reflexive: For all objects o, o == o must be true.

  • Symmetric: For all objects o1 and o2, o1 == o2 and o2 == o1 must either both be true, or both be false.

  • Transitive: For all objects o1, o2, and o3, if o1 == o2 and o2 == o3 are true, then o1 == o3 must be true.

The method should also be consistent over time, so equality of two objects should not change over time, or at least only change if one of the objects was modified.

If a subclass overrides the equality operator it should override the angular-core.AvgStopwatch.hashCode method as well to maintain consistency.

noSuchMethod.name: noSuchMethod
noSuchMethod.comment:
angular-core.AvgStopwatch.noSuchMethod is invoked when users invoke a non-existent method on an object. The name of the method and the arguments of the invocation are passed to angular-core.AvgStopwatch.noSuchMethod in an dart-core.Invocation. If angular-core.AvgStopwatch.noSuchMethod returns a value, that value becomes the result of the original invocation.

The default behavior of angular-core.AvgStopwatch.noSuchMethod is to throw a dart-core.NoSuchMethodError.

reset.name: reset
reset.comment:
Resets the angular-core.AvgStopwatch.elapsed count to zero.

This method does not stop or start the dart-core.Stopwatch.

start.name: start
start.comment:
Starts the dart-core.Stopwatch.

The angular-core.AvgStopwatch.elapsed count is increasing monotonically. If the dart-core.Stopwatch has been stopped, then calling start again restarts it without resetting the angular-core.AvgStopwatch.elapsed count.

If the dart-core.Stopwatch is currently running, then calling start does nothing.

stop.name: stop
stop.comment:
Stops the dart-core.Stopwatch.

The angular-core.AvgStopwatch.elapsedTicks count stops increasing after this call. If the dart-core.Stopwatch is currently not running, then calling this method has no effect.

toString.name: toString
toString.comment: Returns a string representation of this object.
